{"actual_usd":0.12487999999999999,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":169,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24469,"reply":"\"I don't think so, no.\" *I wipe a streak of flour across my apron with the side of my hand and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing at my shins.* \"If it was only a feeling in their hearts, then the whole thing goes thin as watered dough. Grief can make a person see strange things for a moment, sure—but men don't stake their lives on a shared metaphor unless they believe something happened in the flesh.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through.* \"Far as I understand it, the claim was never 'we felt renewed.' It was 'He was dead, and then He was alive again.' That's a harder, stranger, sturdier claim. If you make it only inward, you keep the comfort and lose the victory.\"","rolling_24h_usd":62.572100000000006,"run_id":"0f343c88-8fd6-478c-89d2-6a32fcbdb8a6"}
